<p>Here are three important practices to follow:</p>



<ol>
<li><strong>Firmware Updates</strong>: Regularly check for firmware updates provided by the manufacturer of your hardware wallet. These updates often include important security patches and improvements, ensuring the continued protection of your assets.</li>



<li><strong>Password Management</strong>: Choose a strong, unique password for your hardware wallet and avoid reusing it for other accounts. Consider enabling additional security features such as two-factor authentication for an added layer of protection.</li>



<li><strong>Backup and Recovery</strong>: Regularly create backups of your wallet&#8217;s recovery phrase or seed. Store these backups securely offline, preferably in multiple locations. This ensures that even if your hardware wallet is lost or damaged, you can still recover your funds.</li>
</ol>



<p>Following these security practices will help you maintain the integrity of your Ripple hardware wallet and safeguard your cryptocurrency assets.</p>



