<li><strong>Keep your firmware updated:</strong> Regularly update the firmware of your hardware wallet to ensure it has the latest security features and bug fixes.</li>



<li><strong>Practice good physical security:</strong> Keep your hardware wallet in a secure location, such as a safe or lockbox, to prevent theft or unauthorized access.</li>
</ol>



<p>By following these best practices, you can ensure the long-term security and care of your Ripple hardware wallet, giving you peace of mind as you navigate the world of cryptocurrency storage.</p>



